'''尤里·蓋勒'''（{{Lang-he|אורי גלר }}，{{Lang-en|Uri Geller}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infoplease.com/biography/var/urigeller.html|title=Uri Geller|work=Paranormalist|accessdate=2015-02-27|archive-date=2015-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502093102/http://www.infoplease.com/biography/var/urigeller.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，{{Bd|1946年|12月20日}}），[[以色列|以色列]][[魔術師|魔術師]]。他於[[電視|電視]]演出彎曲湯匙等演出。這些年來，蓋勒已經用簡單的魔術技巧來模擬超感官知覺和心靈感應<ref name="books.google">{{cite journal |title= Geller a fake says ex-manager |author= Randi, James |journal= [[New_Scientist|New Scientist]] |date= 6 April 1978 |page= 11 |volume= 78 |issue= 1097 |url= http://books.google.com/?id=ko7Yy08C1PUC&pg=PA11}}</ref><ref>Reply letter: {{cite journal|title=Geller replies|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=K1N5vdiFwB0C&pg=PA614|issue=1105|volume=78|date=1 June 1978|page=614|author=Geller, Uri|access-date=2015-04-27|archive-date=2014-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101192356/http://books.google.com/books?id=K1N5vdiFwB0C&pg=PA614|dead-url=no}}</ref>。蓋勒的職業生涯已經跨越了超過四十年，並在許多國家演出。

==生平==
蓋勒於1946年12月20日出生在英國託管[[巴勒斯坦託管地|巴勒斯坦]]的[[特拉維夫|特拉維夫]]。他的母親和父親分別為[[奧地利猶太人歷史|奧地利系猶太人]]和匈牙利系猶太人。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-1250577/Me-school-photo-Uri-Geller-remembers-bombs-curfews-shootings-Cyprus.html|title=Me and my school photo: Uri Geller remembers bombs, curfews and shootings in Cyprus|author=Swann, Yvonne|publisher=Mail Online|date=12 February 2010|accessdate=2016-08-09|archive-date=2016-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921082940/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-1250577/Me-school-photo-Uri-Geller-remembers-bombs-curfews-shootings-Cyprus.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>有說法指出蓋勒母親那邊和[[西格蒙德·佛洛伊德|西格蒙德·佛洛伊德]]是遠親。<ref>Margolis, Jonathan (1998) ''Uri Geller Magician or Mystic'', Orion Publishing Group, p. 13, ISBN 0-7528-1006-5.</ref>

==版權問題==
蓋勒為《[[精靈寶可夢系列|精靈寶可夢系列]]》遊戲中的寶可夢，[[勇基拉|勇基拉]]的原型。勇基拉的日文原名ユンゲラー（Yungera）近似於尤里·蓋勒的日語譯名ユリ・ゲラー（Yuri Gera）。而且勇基拉是總拿著湯匙，會使用超能力的寶可夢。2000年11月，蓋勒控告美國[[任天堂|任天堂]]公司<ref>{{cite news|title=Nintendo faces £60m writ from Uri Geller|author=Jonathan Margolis|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/1999/dec/29/2|work=The Guardian|date=1999-01-27|accessdate=2016-12-16|language=en|archive-date=2016-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221121118/https://www.theguardian.com/uk/1999/dec/29/2|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Geller sues Nintendo over Pokémon|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1003454.stm|work=BBC News|publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]|date=2000-11-02|accessdate=2016-12-16|language=en|archive-date=2016-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214042649/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1003454.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此案最終被法院駁回。<ref>{{cite web|title=Game Over: A History of Video Game Lawsuits|url=http://uk.complex.com/pop-culture/2009/11/game-over-a-history-of-video-game-lawsuits|author=Complex Mag|work=Complex UK|date=2009-11-24|accessdate=2016-12-16|language=en|archive-date=2016-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920231153/http://uk.complex.com/pop-culture/2009/11/game-over-a-history-of-video-game-lawsuits|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

2008年，前寶可夢動畫導演[[日高政光|日高政光]]在一次採訪中證實，在與蓋勒達成協議之前，不會在寶可夢卡牌上使用勇基拉。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pokebeach.com/2008/07/second-pokemon-interview-with-masamitsu-hidaka-many-interesting-points|author=Sahagian, Jon|title=Second Interview with Masamitsu Hidaka – Many Interesting Points!|date=4 July 2008|access-date=4 March 2016|publisher=PokéBeach|archive-date=2012-05-20|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/67nVzutdZ?url=http://pokebeach.com/2008/07/second-pokemon-interview-with-masamitsu-hidaka-many-interesting-points|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2020年11月29日，蓋勒在推特上對20年前的行為表示抱歉，同時也解除了對勇基拉的禁令。<ref>{{cite web|author=Solarzano, Sergio|date=28 November 2020|title=Uri Geller Gives Nintendo Permission To Print Kadabra On Pokemon Cards Again|url=https://www.thegamer.com/uri-geller-nintendo-permission-kadabra-pokemon-cards/|access-date=28 November 2020|publisher=The Gamer|archive-date=2021-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410091920/https://www.thegamer.com/uri-geller-nintendo-permission-kadabra-pokemon-cards/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|number=1332794451727691777|user=TheUriGeller|title=I am truly sorry for what I did 20 years ago. Kids and grownups I am releasing the ban. It’s now all up to  #Nintendo to bring my #kadabra #pokemon card back.<br/>It will probably be one of the rarest cards now! Much energy and love to all!<br/>http://urigellermuseum.com|author=Uri Geller|date=28 November 2020}}</ref>

